==English==

===Etymology===
Malaysian for "self-defense". Full name is ''Pencak Silat'', which means "fighting by using techniques of self-defense".

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# A world-wide practiced [[martial art]] involving primarily [[punch]]ing and [[kick]]ing, but additionally, advanced throws, locks, sweeps and trips, grappling and all means of fighting; similar to and borrowing moves from [[karate]], [[Banshay]], [[Krav Maga]] and other Eastern martial arts.

